rComments: Ne prenez pas ce cours, il est un peu fouillis et très vague. Un peu trop globalisant. Les invités ont des sujets inintéressants et tellement nuls. Le professeur est gentil et est prêt à répondre aux questions. Mais ces réponses ne résolvaient pas mes soucis. Je déconseille fortement...
Course was unorganized due to the fact that its new however prof did his best.

J'ai aimé le sujet d'interdisciplinarité et les concepts qu'on a abordé. Par contre, il n'y avait pas de powerpoint ou enregistrement qu'on pouvait se référer durant le cours (visuel avec points clés) ou pour nos révisions d'examen. Les exams et les travaux de groupe sont assez facile.
What is this class? Couldn't tell you if my life depended on it. I read the texts, did the assignment and still have no idea what I am supposed to be learning, if I am learning anything at all.

I still do not know what this class was about to this day. Super ambiguous all the time and no clear course plan or actual course material presented. Seems like a good guy but needs to work on his teaching skills. Whole class is just random philosophical texts that are very hard to interpret with very loose ties between them.

Class was confusing and only received readings. Lectures were difficult to understand in addition to the course content itself. If it weren't for the group projects (worth 45%), I would have definitely failed. Professor was very vague as well when discussing work and the exams.
